# ENCAPSULATION IS THE PROCESS OF COMBINING DATA & FUNCTIONS INTO A SINGLE UNIT CALLED 'CLASS'. IN ENCAPSULATION, THE DATA IS NOT ACCESSED DIRECTLY- IT IS ACCESSED THROUGH THE 
FUNCTIONS PRESENT INSIDE THE CLASS. i.e, 'ATTRIBUTES' OF THE CLASS ARE KEPT 'PRIVATE' AND 'PUBLIC "GETTER" & "SETTER" METHODS' ARE PROVIDED TO MANIPULATE THESE ATTRIBTUES.
# ENCAPSULATION IS USED FOR 'DATA HIDING'
# 'DATA HIDING' IS THE PROCESS OF HIDING DATA OF AN ENTITY(i.e, CLASSES) FROM OTHER ENTITIES.

